article.headline: Austin Peay 70, Morehead State 60
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Maurice Hampton and Adrian Henning led a balanced attack by Austin Peay as the Governors beat Morehead State 70-60 in an Ohio Valley Conference game on Saturday. Hampton and Henning each scored 14 points, and three other Governors scored in double digits as Austin Peay completed a sweep of five road games. The Eagles scored the final seven points in the first half to lead 30-29. The score was tied three times early in the second half, but Austin Peay (8-7, 5-0) took the lead for good at 37-36 with 15:42 remaining on a free throw by Corey Gipson. After that, the Governors led Morehead State (7-8, 2-2) by as many as 12 points. For the Governors, Josh Lewis recorded a double-double with 10 points and 15 rebounds. Rhet Wierzba added 12 points, and Gipson had 11. Morehead State's only scoring threats came from Ricky Minard and Chez Marks. Minard scored the game-high 28 points, and Marks had 21.
